Interface QuadTreeType<T extends QuadTreeMemberType<T>>

    All Known Subinterfaces:

      • quadTreeInsert

        boolean quadTreeInsert(T item)
                throws IllegalArgumentException
        Insert the object item into the quadtree.

        The function returns false if the object could not be inserted for any reason (perhaps due to being too large).

        Parameters:
        item - The object to insert
        Returns:
        true if the object was inserted
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the object's bounding area is not well-formed.
        See Also:
        BoundingAreaCheck.isWellFormed(BoundingAreaType)

      • quadTreeIterateObjects

        <E extends Throwable> void quadTreeIterateObjects(com.io7m.jfunctional.PartialFunctionType<T,Boolean,E> f)
                                           throws E extends Throwable
        Pass each object in the quadtree to f.call(), in no particular order. Iteration stops if f.call() returns false, or raises an exception.
        Type Parameters:
        E - The type of raised exceptions
        Parameters:
        f - The function that will receive each object
        Throws:
        E - Propagated from f.call()
        E extends Throwable

      • quadTreeQueryRaycast

        void quadTreeQueryRaycast(RayI2D ray,
                          SortedSet<QuadTreeRaycastResult<T>> items)
        Returns the objects intersected by the ray ray in items. The objects are returned in order of increasing scalar distance from the origin of ray. That is, the nearest object to the origin of ray will be the first item in items.
        Parameters:
        items - The returned objects
        ray - The ray
        See Also:
        VectorI2D.distance(com.io7m.jtensors.VectorReadable2DType, com.io7m.jtensors.VectorReadable2DType)

        items - The resulting set of quadrants

      • quadTreeRemove

        boolean quadTreeRemove(T item)
        Remove the object item from the quadtree.

        The function returns false if the object could not be removed for any reason (perhaps due to not being in the tree in the first place).

        Parameters:
        item - The object to remove
        Returns:
        true if the object was removed
